> delete_list_openconfig_system_system_dns_servers_server()



OperationId: delete_list_openconfig_system_system_dns_servers_server List of the DNS servers that the resolver should query.  When the resolver is invoked by a calling application, it sends the query to the first name server in this list.  If no response has been received within 'timeout' seconds, the resolver continues with the next server in the list. If no response is received from any server, the resolver continues with the first server again.  When the resolver has traversed the list 'attempts' times without receiving any response, it gives up and returns an error to the calling application.  Implementations MAY limit the number of entries in this list.

# **delete_openconfig_system_system_dns_servers_server**
> delete_openconfig_system_system_dns_servers_server(address)



OperationId: delete_openconfig_system_system_dns_servers_server List of the DNS servers that the resolver should query.  When the resolver is invoked by a calling application, it sends the query to the first name server in this list.  If no response has been received within 'timeout' seconds, the resolver continues with the next server in the list. If no response is received from any server, the resolver continues with the first server again.  When the resolver has traversed the list 'attempts' times without receiving any response, it gives up and returns an error to the calling application.  Implementations MAY limit the number of entries in this list.

OperationId: get_list_openconfig_system_system_dns_servers_server List of the DNS servers that the resolver should query.  When the resolver is invoked by a calling application, it sends the query to the first name server in this list.  If no response has been received within 'timeout' seconds, the resolver continues with the next server in the list. If no response is received from any server, the resolver continues with the first server again.  When the resolver has traversed the list 'attempts' times without receiving any response, it gives up and returns an error to the calling application.  Implementations MAY limit the number of entries in this list.

> GetOpenconfigSystemSystemDnsServersServer get_openconfig_system_system_dns_servers_server(address)



OperationId: get_openconfig_system_system_dns_servers_server List of the DNS servers that the resolver should query.  When the resolver is invoked by a calling application, it sends the query to the first name server in this list.  If no response has been received within 'timeout' seconds, the resolver continues with the next server in the list. If no response is received from any server, the resolver continues with the first server again.  When the resolver has traversed the list 'attempts' times without receiving any response, it gives up and returns an error to the calling application.  Implementations MAY limit the number of entries in this list.

If no response has been received within 'timeout' seconds, the resolver continues with the next server in the list. # **patch_openconfig_system_system_dns_servers_server**
> patch_openconfig_system_system_dns_servers_server(address, body)



OperationId: patch_openconfig_system_system_dns_servers_server List of the DNS servers that the resolver should query.  When the resolver is invoked by a calling application, it sends the query to the first name server in this list.  If no response has been received within 'timeout' seconds, the resolver continues with the next server in the list. If no response is received from any server, the resolver continues with the first server again.  When the resolver has traversed the list 'attempts' times without receiving any response, it gives up and returns an error to the calling application.  Implementations MAY limit the number of entries in this list.

OperationId: post_list_openconfig_system_system_dns_servers_server List of the DNS servers that the resolver should query.  When the resolver is invoked by a calling application, it sends the query to the first name server in this list.  If no response has been received within 'timeout' seconds, the resolver continues with the next server in the list. If no response is received from any server, the resolver continues with the first server again.  When the resolver has traversed the list 'attempts' times without receiving any response, it gives up and returns an error to the calling application.  Implementations MAY limit the number of entries in this list.

> put_openconfig_system_system_dns_servers_server(address, body)



OperationId: put_openconfig_system_system_dns_servers_server List of the DNS servers that the resolver should query.  When the resolver is invoked by a calling application, it sends the query to the first name server in this list.  If no response has been received within 'timeout' seconds, the resolver continues with the next server in the list. If no response is received from any server, the resolver continues with the first server again.  When the resolver has traversed the list 'attempts' times without receiving any response, it gives up and returns an error to the calling application.  Implementations MAY limit the number of entries in this list.
